%N A366343 Numbers k such that every prime power q with q-1 | k-1 is a prime number.
%C A366343 A number k has this property iff every field satisfying x^k = x is a prime field.
%C A366343 Equivalently, every ring satisfying x^k = x is additively generated by idempotents.
%C A366343 These numbers have been called "simple" (see MathOverflow link).
%C A366343 The natural density of the set appears to be approximately 0.462118.
%H A366343 Martin Brandenburg, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.05301">Equational proofs of Jacobson's Theorem</a>, arXiv:2310.05301 [math.RA], 2023.
%H A366343 MathOverflow, <a href="https://mathoverflow.net/questions/455979">Natural density of the set of simple numbers</a>
%o A366343 (SageMath)
%o A366343 def n_powers(n):
%o A366343     """Computes the prime powers q with q-1 | n-1"""
%o A366343     return [x+1 for x in divisors(n-1) if (x+1).is_prime_power()]
%o A366343 def is_simple(n):
%o A366343     """Checks if n is a simple number"""
%o A366343     return n > 1 and all(q.is_prime() for q in n_powers(n))
